body:

It's a simple text search with no regex and no match case, I just have to type one letter and boom everything is freeze.

comment_data.body: Oh!  Does this happen regardless of how many items are in the list?
If I have no log no problem ^^ but once log start coming it freezes, no need to have much in my case. But append every time

Still no news on this ? not being able to search on log is quite annoying :/ if you need more stuff that I can provide I'll gladly provide it :) that search bar is totally useless for now :/ surprise I'm the only on complaining about it lol

Sorry @jaumard.  We've been focussing on language features over the last few quarters (and that's where my attention will be for the foreseeable future).  We've have picked up some work to improve the standard console output since this experimental view is maybe a little further away from being fully production ready.  Not sure if that's useful to you...

Thanks for the nudge!
Hey @pq some news :) still happening with the new version you deployed if you're wondering ^^

Yeah, that'd be my expectation unfortunately.

Have you tried the standard view recently?  It's missing some of the niceties of the structured one but @devoncarew has been adding improvements (most notably to support structured error reporting).
Standard view doesn't have search feature. But I haven't since you put the nice one lool but I've test that structured error reporting and it's quite nice ! :)

milestone.description: Work triaged but not yet planned for a specific release.
